8 An Act relating to the Ethics Commission; amending 74
O.S. 2021, Section 4258, which relates to the Ethics
9 Commission Fund; increasing deposit cap amount;
updating statutory reference; providing an effective
10 date; and declaring an emergency.
11
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 74 O.S. 2021, Section 4258, is
15 amended to read as follows:
16 Section 4258. A. There is hereby created in the State Treasury
17 a revolving fund for the Ethics Commission to be designated the
18 "Ethics Commission Fund". The Ethics Commission Fund shall be a
19 continuing fund, not subject to fiscal year limitations, and
20 deposits to the fund shall consist of the first One Hundred Fifty
21 Thousand Dollars ($150,000.00) Two Hundred Fifty Thousand Dollars
22 ($250,000.00) of fees received by the Commission each fiscal year.
23 Fees collected each fiscal year in excess of One Hundred Fifty
24 Thousand Dollars ($150,000.00) Two Hundred Fifty Thousand Dollars
ENGR. H. B. NO. 4037 Page 1

1 ($25 0,000.00) shall be placed to the credit of the Ethics Commission
2 Online Filing Revolving Fund created pursuant to Section 2 4258.2 of
3 this act title.
4 B. All monies accruing to the credit of the Ethics Commission
5 Fund are hereby appropriated and may be budgeted and expended by the
6 Commission for any expenses incurred in the implementation of its
7 duties as provided by law. Expenditures from the fund shall be made
8 upon warrants issued by the State Treasurer against claims filed as
9 prescribed by law with the Director of the Office of Management and
10 Enterprise Services for approval and payment.
11 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
12 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
13 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
14 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
15 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
16 Passed the House of Representatives the 14th day of April, 2026.
